title: Man extradited from Pakistan and charged with murder over 2005 killing of PC Sharon Beshenivsky
description: A man has been extradited from Pakistan and charged with the murder of PC Sharon Beshenivsky, the Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) has said.

title: Sales soar at luxury firm headed by world's richest man
description: The world's richest man Bernard Arnault has received a boost after his luxury goods company LVMH reported a 17% rise in global sales.

title: Mane punched Sane in face after Bayern Munich's loss to Man City
description: Bayern Munich's Sadio Mane punched teammate Leroy Sane in the face after the team's defeat to Manchester City.

title: Supporters of Sikh separatists 'misusing' UK asylum system to help terrorism, says India
description: India has asked Britain for increased monitoring of UK-based supporters of a Sikh separatist movement as it accuses them of abusing the asylum system to help "terrorist activities" in the South Asia country.

title: Trump accuses his 'friend' Macron of 'kissing Chinese president's a**'
description: Donald Trump has accused French President Emmanuel Macron of "kissing Xi Jinping's a**" during his recent visit to Beijing.

title: Zelenskyy condemns Russian 'beasts' as video appears to show soldier beheading Ukrainian
description: A gruesome video appearing to show a Ukrainian captive being beheaded by a Russian soldier has been condemned by Volodymyr Zelenskyy.

title: Small boat crossings 'linked to sharp rise in UK diphtheria cases'
description: A "sharp increase" in cases of diphtheria in the UK and across Europe has been linked to small boat crossings, research has found.

title: 'Net closing' on Russian elite as new sanctions target Abramovich and Usmanov fixers
description: Fresh sanctions have been placed on those helping Russian oligarchs continue to do business in the UK - including fixers for Roman Abramovich and ex-Arsenal FC shareholder Alisher Usmanov.

title: Children 'among 100 dead' as Myanmar military targets village event
description: Myanmar's military has confirmed it carried out an airstrike on a village event as part of an attack which is thought to have killed up to 100 people, including children.

title: Taiwan claims China is getting ready to 'launch a war'
description: China seems to be getting "ready to launch a war" against Taiwan, according to a senior politician from the island nation.

title: What the Pentagon leaks reveal about the war in Ukraine
description: The Pentagon is racing to find the source behind the leaking of a slew of highly classified military documents about the Ukraine war.

title: First human death from H3N8 bird flu recorded in China
description: A woman in China has become the first person to die from a type of bird flu that is rare in humans, the World Health Organisation (WHO) has said.

title: Israeli army shoots dead two alleged Palestinian gunmen in West Bank
description: The Israeli military killed two Palestinians who authorities said allegedly opened fire at troops from their car in the northern West Bank on Tuesday.

title: Mexico immigration agency chief to face charges after fire killed 40 migrants
description: The head of Mexico's immigration agency will face criminal charges for a fire that killed 40 migrants in a locked cell at a detention centre near the border with the US.

title: Ministry of Defence hits back after claim UK special forces are in Ukraine
description: The Ministry of Defence says there is "a serious level of inaccuracy" in leaks which claim UK special forces have been operating in Ukraine.

title: Ministry of Defence refuses to deny UK special forces have been operating in Ukraine
description: The Ministry of Defence has refused to deny UK special forces have been operating in Ukraine after US classified military documents were allegedly leaked and published online.
